tasks.description:
The ErrorResultFile.tsx generates ErrorResult<T> extending Response<T> (Azure) or ClientResult<T> (unbranded). For Azure flavor, Response<T> inherits from NullableResponse<T> which has an abstract GetRawResponse() method. The generated ErrorResult does not override it, causing CS0534.

Generated code (broken):
```csharp
internal partial class ErrorResult<T> : Response<T>
{
    private readonly Response _response;
    private readonly RequestFailedException _exception;
    public ErrorResult(Response response, RequestFailedException exception) : base(default, response) { ... }
    public override T Value => throw _exception;
    // MISSING: public override Response GetRawResponse() => _response;
}
```

Fix: Add a conditional GetRawResponse() override in the ErrorResult component when flavor is Azure:
```csharp
public override Response GetRawResponse() => _response;
```

This is a small, surgical fix in ErrorResultFile.tsx.

Reference files:
- src/components/infrastructure/ErrorResultFile.tsx (85 lines — the component)
- src/utils/pipeline-types.ts (pipelineTypes.response is Azure.Response for azure flavor)
- temp/e2e/Spector/http/azure/core/basic/src/Generated/Internal/ErrorResult.cs (generated output showing the missing override)

The emit-e2e.ts script discovers ARM specs from @azure-tools/azure-http-specs/specs/azure/resource-manager/ but only passes `flavor=azure`. ARM specs require `management=true` to activate ARM-specific code generation (resource detection, Resource/Collection classes, extensions, etc.).

Current code (eng/scripts/emit-e2e.ts lines 311-313):
```typescript
if (spec.source === "azure") {
  args.push("--option", "http-client-csharp.flavor=azure");
}
```

Required change: detect ARM specs and add management options:
```typescript
if (spec.source === "azure") {
  args.push("--option", "http-client-csharp.flavor=azure");
  const specDir = spec.outputDir ?? dirname(spec.relativePath);
  if (specDir.startsWith("azure/resource-manager/")) {
    args.push("--option", "http-client-csharp.management=true");
    args.push("--option", "http-client-csharp.enable-wire-path-attribute=true");
  }
}
```

Also update VERSIONED_SPECS if any ARM specs need versioned compilation, and add any needed ALIAS_OVERRIDES for ARM spec disambiguation.

After this change, run `pnpm emit:e2e --filter azure/resource-manager/common-properties` to verify ARM spec generation works.

Reference files:
- eng/scripts/emit-e2e.ts (compileSpec function ~line 280, VERSIONED_SPECS ~line 130)
- eng/scripts/emit-mgmt.ts (management plane emit script — shows correct management options)
- src/options.ts (management option definition)
- src/emitter.tsx (how management=true triggers ARM resource detection and code generation)
